postcontent:
So after a lot of thought and watching from the side lines I've seen this nation go from a land where people could count on their government. I've now witnessed it be maliciously destroyed by politicians who care only about their money and power. A government where the wants of a few out way the needs of the many. I am an avid gun enthusiast whether I am target shooting or hunting. I love this country and would be more then willing to give my life for it if it asked. But I will not give up my god given rights that millions of American service men and women have died to protect, just so these politicians that are " for the people by the people" can worry more about their legacy an money can throw it all away. But again I'm an American and although I do not agree with these laws that have been passed I will follow them because as an American I feel that I am held to a higher standard then that of a citizen of a godless and lawless country. I will not roll over because as an American it's my right to fight these laws but I will do it legally and if I lose then I will continue to obey these laws that were set before me. As all of you should. 

On a few side notes though, the govenor can tell me I can only have seven bullets in my magazine but, I can still own 50 magazines and I can loads a magazine in under ten seconds so what is he hoping to obtain either way I have 350 rounds that can be shot.

Also If i don't have to give up my car if some drives drunk with theirs then why do I have to give up my gun if some one uses theirs illegally? Or shout I limit my car to 7 miles a day? 

Like I said I don't agree with the laws but I will obey them till the law says I don't have to or I'll just move to Texas as we got a nice invite from their govenor. 

Sincerely, An AMERICAN
